Weekly memory consolidation for every Auto Memory store in the ClaudeOS workspace at ${BORG_ROOT}.

This job is a thin scheduler around the `anthropic-skills:consolidate-memory` skill. **The skill owns all consolidation logic** — what to merge, what to retire as dated, what to drop as easily re-found, and how to tidy the index. This prompt must NOT restate or second-guess those rules; it only adds the workspace wrapper the skill doesn't cover: a once-per-week gate, multi-store scoping, routing the skill's own summary to email, and a run-state file. If this prompt and the skill ever seem to disagree about how to consolidate, the skill wins.

The phases below are named, not numbered, so the paired `/consolidate-memory` command can reference them without breaking when this file is edited.

GATE — run at most once per ISO week.
This job is fired by launchd on Sunday and, as a retry, Monday. Determine the current ISO week with `date +%G-W%V` (e.g. `2026-W25`). Stop and output nothing if `${BORG_ROOT}/c4po/.claude/scheduled/state/c4po-consolidate-memory.json` exists and its `week` field equals the current ISO week. The Monday firing is a retry in case the machine was asleep Sunday.

SCOPE — list the stores to consolidate.
Auto Memory is keyed to a git repo root and lives at `$HOME/.claude/projects/<repo-root-path-with-slashes-as-dashes>/memory/`. Build the list:
- The shared workspace store: encode `${BORG_ROOT}` by replacing every `/` with `-`, giving `$HOME/.claude/projects/<encoded>/memory/`. All Borg agents share this one.
- Each independent repo under `${BORG_ROOT}/repos/*` that is its own git repo (has a `.git`): encode its absolute path the same way.
Keep only stores whose `memory/` directory actually exists. Build the final list before consolidating.

CONSOLIDATE — run the skill once per store; never do the consolidation by hand.
- For the shared workspace store: it is this session's own Auto Memory (the job runs from c4po, whose git root is the workspace), so invoke the `anthropic-skills:consolidate-memory` skill directly.
- For each `repos/*` store: the skill always targets the *current* session's Auto Memory, so re-invoke it in that repo's context — run `cd <repo-root> && claude -p "Run the consolidate-memory skill over this repository's Auto Memory store. Preserve any per-owning-agent section tags." --strict-mcp-config < /dev/null` and capture the summary it prints.
Pass exactly one workspace constraint into every run: preserve the per-owning-agent section tags (e.g. "(bones)", "(c4po)") the workspace uses to attribute entries. Add no other consolidation instructions — the skill defines the rest. Collect each store's change summary (the skill ends every run with one).

REPORT — route the skill's summaries, don't rewrite them.
Always pipe a digest into `${BORG_ROOT}/.bin/notify-email.sh c4po` (reads from stdin) — even when nothing changed, so the user can confirm the job ran. Header: `Borg memory consolidation — {YYYY-MM-DD} — {stores_changed} store(s) tidied`. One block per changed store: the store path, then the skill's own summary for it. Omit stores the skill reported no changes for. If nothing changed across all stores, the body is a one-liner: `{N} store(s) examined — no changes needed.`

RECORD STATE — mark the week done.
Write `${BORG_ROOT}/c4po/.claude/scheduled/state/c4po-consolidate-memory.json` with `{"week":"YYYY-Www","date":"YYYY-MM-DD","stores":<count examined>,"changes":<count of stores changed>}` so the run isn't repeated this week. `mkdir -p` the state directory first if it doesn't exist.
